    "name": "FDA 510(k) FEA Acceptability Requirement for Spinal Implants",
    "description": "Per FDA guidance on the use of FEA in 510(k) submissions for spinal implants (FDA-2019-D-3404), computational model predictions must be validated against physical bench tests using ASTM F1717 or equivalent. Acceptance criteria require that all predicted quantities of interest fall within 10% of experimental mean values and that the normalized validation metric E/uval remain below 1.96. The model credibility level must meet or exceed the required level derived from model risk and decision consequence per ASME V&V 40-2018.",
    "source": "https://www.fda.gov/regulatory-information/search-fda-guidance-documents/assessing-credibility-computational-modeling-through-verification-and-validation-application",
    "regulatoryBasis": "21 CFR Part 820; FDA Guidance on Assessing Credibility of Computational Modeling (2021)"
  },
