      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented V&V procedures. FDA and DePuy Synthes internal SQA records confirm ISO 9001-compliant software lifecycle controls. Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10.1 were executed and results archived. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed using manufactured solutions for linear elastic beam bending and contact problems representative of the pedicle screw geometry. Convergence of discretization error to theoretical order confirmed. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Mesh convergence study required with GCI < 1%.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three mesh densities (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 118k elements, fine: 341k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI for stiffness QoI = 0.61%, yield force QoI = 0.83%. Both below 1% threshold. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residuals (tolerance 1e-6). Newton-Raphson iteration converged within 12 increments for all load cases. No divergence or spurious oscillation observed. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application performed by a second analyst not involved in original model construction. Discrepancies reviewed and resolved. Simulation log files archived. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Model physics must capture dominant deformation mechanisms.",
      "rationale": "Continuum nonlinear elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening applied to Ti-6Al-4V screw and UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) modeled at all interfaces. Geometric nonlinearity (large deformation) enabled. Dominant mechanisms — bending-induced plasticity at screw-rod junction and construct compliance — are captured. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Material properties must be sourced from traceable measurements.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E=114 GPa, yield 880 MPa, UTS 950 MPa) sourced from coupon tensile tests on material from same heat lot as test constructs. UHMWPE block properties from supplier certification. Dimensional inputs from CMM measurements of 5 representative screws. Uncertainty in material properties propagated via Monte Carlo (n=500). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. N≥10 samples required; samples must be from production lot.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: n=6; Lab 2: n=5). All constructs assembled from production-representative components. Lot traceability documented. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; no significant systematic bias detected (p=0.31, Welch t-test). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Multiple test conditions spanning the intended use envelope required.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration (5 mm offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). No variation in load rate, temperature, or offset distance explored. This limits coverage of the intended use envelope and results in achieved level 2, which is below the required level of 3. This is a known gap acknowledged by the assessment team; the gap is partially offset by strong performance on all other factors and by the conservative nature of the single test condition relative to in vivo loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Model inputs must be demonstrably equivalent to test conditions.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in FEA replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as verified by direct comparison to fixture drawings. Load application point, constraint locations, and offset distance match test setup to within CMM measurement uncertainty. Material lot traceability ensures equivalency of constitutive inputs to physical specimens. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Quantitative comparison with uncertainty quantification required.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm). Normalized validation metric E/uval computed for each QoI incorporating experimental uncertainty (measurement repeatability, inter-laboratory variability) and model uncertainty (material property uncertainty, geometric uncertainty). All E/uval values below 1.96 (0.43, 0.71, 0.38 respectively). Graphical force-displacement overlay provided for all 11 specimens. Achieved level 4 exceeds required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. QoIs must directly support the regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the QoIs specified in FDA guidance for spinal implant FEA submissions and are directly linked to the 510(k) substantial equivalence determination. Each QoI maps to a distinct failure mode (fatigue initiation, plastic deformation, construct integrity). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3. Validation scenario must be representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, production constructs, two independent laboratories) is directly representative of the COU. The same FEA model configuration, material assignments, and boundary conditions used in validation are used in the submission predictions. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
